<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE REDUCTION, SINGLE SPEED AXLES: SPICER D135-S,
        F155-S, F170-S SERIES - REMOVE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
            <title>CARRIER FROM AXLE HOUSING</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Steam clean axle assembly before removing rear carrier.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove drain plug and drain lubricant.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect drive shaft at rear U-joint.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If pinion or pinion bearings are to be removed, break loose pinion nut at this time.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove axle shaft bolts and lockwasher, or stud nuts and cone locks. Remove axle shafts.
                    If a gasket is assembled between the hub and shaft, discard the old gasket and replace with a new
                    one at the time of assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support the carrier on a roller jack.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the carrier-to-housing bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Break the carrier loose from the housing. Use pry bars behind the carrier flange
                    mounting face if necessary.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove carrier assembly from the housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount the carrier assembly in a suitable rebuild stand or place on a sturdy work
                    bench.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
